“While several risks currently impede broad adoption of <a class="link" href="https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fdlt&amp;trk=public_post_reshare-text" target="_self" data-tracking-control-name="public_post_reshare-text" data-tracking-will-navigate>#DLT</a>, wholesale <a class="link" href="https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fcbdc&amp;trk=public_post_reshare-text" target="_self" data-tracking-control-name="public_post_reshare-text" data-tracking-will-navigate>#CBDC</a> on a private permissioned <a class="link" href="https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fblockchain&amp;trk=public_post_reshare-text" target="_self" data-tracking-control-name="public_post_reshare-text" data-tracking-will-navigate>#blockchain</a> could overcome existing risks and impediments - and lead to significant efficiency gains in the financial system across debt capital markets,” stated Josselin.
